Food tourism and experiences: Work is underway to develop some new food trails starting at QVM, encouraging people to explore the incredible things that regional food social enterprises have to offer.
Participation and collaboration: The site offers a real opportunity for people to come and roll up their sleeves, put on an apron, learn and share. E-learning modules will also be developed to help would-be food innovators test and create new retail-ready circular products.[]{'Instagram': 'https://www.instagram.com/purposeprecinct/', 'Facebook': 'https://www.facebook.com/purposeprecinct/', 'Email': 'mailto:hello@movingfeast.net', 'Website': 'https://movingfeast.net/projects/queen-victoria-market-purpose-precinct'}

Sovereign Foods is a community-built, employee-run, not-for-profit initiative created to support community food systems based on transparency, sustainability and self-determination. Our work began in food co-operatives and bulk buying groups in Brisbane, trying to source local, ethical and sustainable produce with our friends and families.
Sovereign Foods was created in support of the food sovereignty movement, ascribing to the values that we, as food eaters, have the right to define our own food system. We choose to purchase exclusively from local farming families to ensure you know who grew your food and how they grew it so you have a choice in what you eat.Our mission is to put people, ethics and sustainability at the heart of Australia's food system. We aim to contribute to the health of local communities: economically, socially, and environmentally.
We will do this by:
Supporting smallholder farmers with roots in their community, growing food in an ecologically sustainable manner;
Creating avenues for people to access this food affordably; and
Helping to develop vibrant, transparent local food networks.[]{'Instagram': 'https://www.instagram.com/sovereignfoodsau/', 'Facebook': 'https://www.facebook.com/sovereignfoodsau', 'Email': 'mailto:contact.us@sovereignfoods.com.au', 'Website': 'https://sovereignfoods.com.au/'}

Lil's Yolky Dokey Eggs is a pasture-raised, real free-range egg business based in Main Ridge on the Mornington Peninsula. We keep the number of hens to fewer than 60 hens per hectare and pride ourselves on this low stock density that results in happy hens and quality eggs. Our Gypsy chickens live in the best conditions out in open pastures under the close protection of our Maremma dogs as their guardians. They roam free during the day and sleep in their caravans at night.
We currently service 40-plus stockists across the Mornington Peninsula, and we cannot keep up with demand, even though we have expanded the business fourfold since we began in 2018. We run a small Farm Gate, and our farm is part of a collective of farmers who farm following the regenerative model. Our chickens follow the cattle and fertilise the land as they go while scratching the cow dung and eating insect pests along the way.Lil’s Yolky Dokey Eggs is currently refining the systems and processes required to run a successful business. We are hoping to mentor farmers who are interested in growing pasture-raised eggs on their property. By doing this, we believe that we will be contributing towards the growth in food security on the Mornington Peninsula and creating a quality product that will be available to the community.
The more farmers we have on the Mornington Peninsula, the better it will be for the community and ongoing food security.[]{'Instagram': 'https://www.instagram.com/yolkydokey/?hl=en', 'Facebook': 'https://www.facebook.com/Lils-Yolky-Dokey-Eggs-1802470646728191/', 'Email': 'mailto:yolkydokey@bigpond.com', 'Website': 'https://www.yolkydokey.com.au/'}

NutriSoil is a proudly family-owned business located in northern Victoria. Our innovative and impact-driven team generate a vibrant culture, who are maintaining an influential, industry-leading brand in nature-based quality vermiculture products to support regenerative agriculture and sustainability.
NutriSoil’s vermiculture products are made through a unique vermiwash recycling system. Our liquid vermiwash is a biological stimulant containing an abundance of microbes and other essential compounds needed for plant health, and is used to support farmers' transition to a synthetic-free production system, building carbon levels on the way to profitable farming systems.
Our purpose is to support the next generation of agriculture to produce healthy soil and food. We are achieving this through not only our quality products, but through our unique Hub Care program, which supports farmers on their journey to rebuild soil health and function.NutriSoil invests heavily in education to support all farmers in their understanding of the relationship between plants, microbes, nutrients and soil. NutriSoil provides support through online webinars, courses, face-to-face events and ongoing podcasts to meet our objectives. NutriSoil is passionate about the long-term sustainability of Australian agriculture and farms. Our support programs are designed to increase knowledge and understanding to improve soil organic matter, soil carbon and biology to create functional soils for the future. Currently, we are also expanding our production facilities to ensure we continue to meet future demands for our product and services.[]{'Instagram': 'https://www.instagram.com/nutrisoilbiologicalsolution/', 'Facebook': 'https://www.facebook.com/nutrisoil/', 'Email': 'mailto:nakala@nutrisoil.com.au', 'Website': 'https://www.nutrisoil.com.au/'}

Since 2006 we’ve operated a traditional, whole animal butchery, sourcing pasture-raised animals directly from regeneratively-managed, local farms fostering fertility, biodiversity and resilience. Our goal is to transform passive customers into active agents for better land, animal and human welfare through storytelling and retail experiences that build connection and understanding of our place in nature.
Through our two butcheries, online shop and kitchen, we use every part of every animal we source, promote a balanced diet and run our business according to a set of core principles established in 2006. We prioritise heritage breeds, everything we sell is labelled with the farm and the breed and we don't make any claims we can't substantiate. We visit every farm we work with to understand each unique situation so we can represent the farmers' practice properly to our customers.
In 2020, we published our first book, ‘The Ethical Omnivore’.We run regular whole animal butchery classes and host events with advocates and writers in the regenerative food space. We’re currently working on a series of events with 2022 Bob Hawke National Landcare award winner and respected regenerative farmer, Bruce Maynard.[]{'Instagram': 'https://www.instagram.com/featherandboneprovidore/', 'Facebook': 'https://www.facebook.com/Feather-and-Bone-Providore-179031158816077/', 'Email': 'mailto:laura@featherandbone.com.au', 'Website': 'https://featherandbone.com.au/'}

